TY  - GEN
TI  - Anxiety and Depression from Cybervictimization in Adolescents: A Metaanalysis and Meta-regression Study
AU  - M. M. Molero
AU  - África Martos
AU  - A. B. Barragán
AU  - M. C. Pérez-Fuentes
AU  - J. J. Gázquez
PY  - 2022
UR  - https://journals.copmadrid.org/ejpalc/archivos/1889_1861_ejpalc_14_1_0042.pdf
DO  - 10.5093/ejpalc2022a5
JO  - European Journal of Psychology Applied to Legal Context
AB  - Meta-analysis of 13 cross-sectional studies (N = 7,348 adolescents) on cybervictimization, anxiety, and depression. Found moderate-to-large correlations: r = .31 for anxiety and r = .28 for depression. Girls and certain geographic regions showed stronger effects. **Methodology:** Meta-analysis (cross-sectional studies only); meta-regression for moderators. **Limitations:** All included studies are cross-sectional — causal direction cannot be established; moderate heterogeneity expected.
