TY  - GEN
TI  - Social comparison and state–trait dynamics: Viewing image-conscious Instagram accounts affects college students’ mood and anxiety.
AU  - Madison T. Kohler
AU  - Imani N. Turner
AU  - G. Webster
PY  - 2021
UR  - https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/8b20bf72c6839d169661af4952165b38b504f2c1
DO  - 10.1037/ppm0000310
JO  - Psychology of Popular Media
AB  - Randomized experiment (N = 81 undergraduates) where participants were assigned to scroll either image-conscious Instagram accounts (fitness/beauty/model) or control accounts (food/nature). Viewing image-conscious content caused decreased positive mood and increased anxiety. People with lower trait anxiety were paradoxically more susceptible to state anxiety increases. **Methodology:** Randomized experimental pre/post design; state/trait anxiety measures. **Limitations:** Small sample; university students, not minors; single-session exposure not representative of real-world cumulative use.
